    <h2>What each type can and cannot do</h2>

    <p>This is the core of the guard rails. Missing cells are not accidents — they are deliberate design choices:</p>

    <div class="not-prose my-8 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
            <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Capability</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold text-center">Instant</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold text-center">LocalDate</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold text-center">LocalTime</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold text-center">LocalDateTime</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold text-center">ZonedDateTime</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-gray-400">
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2">Add/subtract Duration</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-green-400">yes</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-red-400/60">no</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-green-400">yes</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-red-400/60">no</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-green-400">yes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2">Add days/months/years</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-brand-400">+ tz</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-green-400">yes</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-red-400/60">no</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-center text-red-400/60">no</td>
